│ were not defined. Also, the loop iterators were different (`BasicBlock&` vs `BasicBlock*`), causing type mismatches.         │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The fundamental idea remains correct: the Control Flow Graph (CFG) must be cleaned up *before* dead blocks are collected for │
│ deletion. The original code collects dead blocks based on reachability information (`isBlockExecutable`) and only later      │
│ updates the CFG itself (removing predecessor edges for blocks that become unreachable due to non-returning calls). This      │
│ ordering is what causes the crash.                                                                                           │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ To fix this, I will reorder the logic within the `runIPSCCP` function in `llvm/lib/Transforms/IPO/SCCP.cpp`. I will move the │
│ CFG cleanup logic to execute before the dead block collection logic. However, this time I will be careful to keep the code   │
│ within the correct scope where all necessary variables are accessible.                                                       │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ The correct order of operations should be:                                                                                   │
│ 1.  Run the IPSCCP solver.                                                                                                   │
│ 2.  Perform CFG cleanup: for any block that the solver found to be unreachable, change its terminator to `unreachable` and   │
│ remove it from the predecessor lists of its successors.                                                                      │
│ 3.  Collect dead blocks: now that the CFG is consistent, collect all blocks that have no predecessors.                       │
│ 4.  Delete the collected dead blocks and their successors.                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ I will use `sed` to perform this reordering. I will cut the block of code responsible for collecting `BBsWithNoPreds` and    │
│ paste it after the block of code that performs the CFG cleanup. This ensures the cleanup happens first, resolving the bug    │
│ without introducing compilation errors.                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                              │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                      │
│ sed -i -e '219,225d' -e '241a\' -e '# Find all blocks that are not reachable.\nSmallVector<BasicBlock *, 16>                 │
│ BBsWithNoPreds;\nfor (Function &F : M)\n  if (!F.isDeclaration())\n    for (BasicBlock &BB : F)\n      if                    │
